Let's think step by step. Let us assume that Daria starts working at time $t$. Before she joins, Amy, Bomani, and Charlie will have packed $(60-t)\cdot \frac{4}{3}+(60-t)(3)+(60-t)\cdot 3=180-2t$ packages, so after Daria has been working for $(75-t)$ minutes, all four workers would have packed $$180-2t+\frac{4}{3}(75-t)+75-t+5(75-t)=450$$packages. This yields the equation \begin{align*}
\frac{4}{3}(75-t)+(180-2t)+75+t+5(75-t)&amp;=450\\
\Rightarrow\qquad 100-\frac{2}{3}t&amp;=195\\
\Rightarrow\qquad t &amp;=\boxed{\textbf{(B)}\ 95}.
\end{align*}

The answer is B.
